[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hillhead Jordanhill Ladies rugby team in bus crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Members of a women's rugby team have escaped serious injury after their bus crashed down an embankment.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Hillhead Jordanhill Ladies team were returning to Glasgow after a Scottish Cup quarter final match in Dumfries against Stewartry Sirens.
Their vehicle left the A701 Dumfries to Moffat road on a bend at Blackacre near Parkgate.
Everyone was able to walk away from the bus relatively uninjured and the team have all arrived in Glasgow.
Police said four people had been taken to hospital after the crash and the bus driver was kept in overnight for observation.
